<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>climb up the wall • go over the wall</xh5><p> <i>climb up the wall</i>—<i>(coll.)</i> become very angry or distraught: Old Marks will <u>climb up the wall</u> if he hears I closed early.</p><p><i>go over the wall</i>—1. leave a religious order: The world is always more interested in the one nun who <u>goes over the wall</u> than the thousands who don’t. 2. escape from prison: Us guys pull wires to get jobs as guards, and you convicts <u>go over the wall</u> whenever you can. 3. defect to another country: The bloody place [the Foreign Office] has never been the same since Kim Philby <u>went over the wal</u>l. 4. go to prison: He would be observed “<u>going over the wal</u>l” or “going to stir” (going to detention prison).</p> </entry>
